            . I live with my mother, Martha Gardiner, in <placeName id="t18280703-159-crimeloc796">Chiswell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280703-159-crimeloc796" type="placeName" value="Chiswell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280703-159-crimeloc796" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-159-off794 t18280703-159-crimeloc796"></join>. I was told a person had taken a hat from a rail inside the door - I went after the prisoner: I found her opposite Bunhill-row with it under her shawl - I took her to the watch-house; she said, I could only lag her for seven years, and then she should come out sweet and fresh.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-159-person927">
                  MARY 
